In this briefing, White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs announces that DHS Secretary Napolitano and John Brennan, the Director of the White House Homeland Security Council, will be visiting border communities to enhance border security and cooperation with Mexico and local law enforcement. He also discusses the President's schedule for the upcoming week, including meetings with FDIC and Fed officials, a transportation event, and the President's trip to Mexico and the Summit of the Americas. Gibbs provides updates on the Somali piracy incident and the administration's strategy towards addressing piracy. He also discusses the upcoming economic meeting, the stress tests for banks, and the administration's position on immigration reform. Other topics covered include defense costs, interest rates, charitable deductions, church attendance, and the President's stance on the state secrets privilege.